main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in Garwood, New Jersey on December 31, 1969.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 2 minutes, The observer noted one object hovering and then suddenly accelerating out of sight, The object was approximately 30 feet in diameter and bright white in color, The object was observed at an angle of about 30 degrees above the horizon on a clear night, The observer reported a silvery-gray dull glow from the object.
witness description: the observer has several previous sightings
